The paper deals with visual recognition tasks using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of kernels to model invariance, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The methodology proposed in the paper involves training the CNN to approximate the kernel feature map, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its methodology on visual recognition tasks, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
